descriptions.description: A magical adventure land with a flying bus, fortune tellers, the Mirror Maze of Insanity and much more. Meet everyone's favourite ogre and spend a special day out with lots of fun.

Embark on a delightful adventure through the magic of Covent Garden! Dive into the charm and mystery of this iconic area with two playful, treasure-hunt-style walks that are brimming with surprises. Whether you’re young, old, or somewhere in between, you’ll spot fascinating things you’ve never noticed before – from quirky landmarks to hidden gems.

Curious About Covent Garden will take you beyond the obvious attractions to uncover the unusual and extraordinary. Perfect for families, couples, or solo explorers, each walk lasts 1–2 hours and guarantees fresh air and fun. In your handy 16-page booklet, you’ll find:

Two captivating walking routes with clear maps and directions.

Intriguing clues to solve (don’t worry – hints are provided, and answers are at the back!).

Fun challenges like identifying pictures and uncovering fascinating snippets about Covent Garden’s history, people, and events.

Places you will pass (& may want to stop off) on the way include:

The enchanting Seven Dials.

Bustling Covent Garden Market.

The fascinating London Transport Museum.

Majestic Somerset House.

The iconic Covent Garden Opera House.

The vibrant energy of The Strand.

Explore the area at your own pace! Choose between the printed booklet (delivered to your door) or the instant download (print at home or save on your mobile device). And here’s the cherry on top: Use code List20 at checkout for 20% off! all purchases

Ready to extend your adventure? Check out other London walks in St Paul’s, Soho, Mayfair, and Trafalgar Square. So gather your family or friends, and let the curious explorer in you shine. It’s time to Explore, Discover, Enjoy Covent Garden like never before!

descriptions.description: Buddy (Ferrell) is a big Elf who, though accepted in his Elvish community at the North Pole, manages to wreak havoc on a daily basis. Fed up and confused by his charge, Papa Elf (Bob Newhart) sends him to the US in search of his true identity. Hilarious and puerile Yuletide comedy.

Starring Will Ferrell and Zooey Deschanel (New Girl) and directed by Jon Favreau (Jungle Book, Iron Man), Elf has become a modern Christmas classic and must-see each holiday season.

Enjoy Elf on the big screen this year and meet our very own Customs House elves, who will make sure you feel welcome with a gift and tasty treat.
